-- Clermont, Toulon, Munster, Wasps Win in European Rugby's Heineken Cup
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-12-12T17:29:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-12/clermont-toulon-munster-wasps-win-in-european-rugby-s-heineken-cup.html
There were wins for Clermont
Auvergne, Toulon, Munster and Wasps today in European rugby’s
Heineken Cup.  Munster captain Paul O’Connell was red-carded in the 22-16
victory over Ospreys after a clash with opposing No. 8 Jonathan
Thomas. O’Connell’s team won with tries by Doug Howlett, David
Wallace and Johne Murphy and tops Pool 3.  WEEKEND RESULTS
==============  Pool 1: Castres 21-16 Edinburgh; Northampton 23-15 Cardiff.
Pool 2: Saracens 21-24 Racing Metro; Clermont Auvergne 20-13
Leinster.
Pool 3: London Irish 13-19 Toulon; Munster 22-16 Ospreys.
Pool 4: Aironi 28-27 Biarritz; Ulster 22-18 Bath.
Pool 5: Perpignan 24-19 Leicester; Scarlets 35-27 Treviso.
Pool 6: Glasgow 16-28 Toulouse; Newport-Gwent 16-23 Wasps.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
